# Figures

This directory contains the principal figures generated during the cross-species therapeutic target discovery workflow.

| Figure | Description |
|---|---|
| `Figure0_Project_Workflow.png` | Overview of the discovery, validation, and consensus-prioritization workflow. |
| `Figure1_Human_AMP_LN_Atlas.png` | Annotated UMAP of the human AMP lupus nephritis single-cell atlas. |
| `Figure2_Human_Lead_Targets_DotPlot.png` | Expression specificity and prevalence of the four prioritized targets across human cell populations. |
| `Figure3_Target_UMAPs.png` | UMAP feature plots showing the distribution of the four prioritized targets in the human atlas. |
| `Figure4_Cross_Dataset_Evidence_Matrix.png` | Transparent summary of evidence from human scRNA-seq, mouse scRNA-seq, human spatial analysis, and spatial macrophage correlation. |
| `Figure5_Consensus_Target_Ranking.png` | Positive additive consensus score for the four final targets; maximum possible score is 4. |
| `Supplementary_Figure1_Mouse_Candidate_Targets_DotPlot.png` | Broader mouse candidate-target panel used during exploratory cross-species validation. |

## Interpretation of evidence weights

- `1.0`: supported by the corresponding analysis
- `0.5`: partial or suggestive support
- `0.0`: not supported or not directly available

The main consensus score is an additive evidence count. It avoids standardized negative values, which can be misleading when the objective is to summarize the amount of supporting evidence.

## Reproducibility

Figures 4 and 5 are regenerated by `scripts/05_consensus_ranking.R` from `results/Consensus_Target_Ranking.csv`.
